{
  "text": "The CFTR protein was detected by western blotting, as reported by [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] using the mouse 596 monoclonal antibody (Cystic Fibrosis Foundation Therapeutics Inc, Bethesda, MD, USA), which detects the NBD2 domain; [CITATION_3] the secondary antibody was an anti-mouse IgG (NA 931 V, GE Healthcare/Amersham, Freiburg, Germany). Detection was by ECL, using western blotting detection reagent RPN 2106 Amersham GE Healthcare. Blots were reprobed with a mouse anti-a-tubulin (B-7) monoclonal antibody (sc-5286, Santa Cruz Biotechnology Inc, Santa Cruz, CA, USA), as loading controls.",
  "correct_citation": {
